                <h2 class="subheading">Step-by-Step Guide to Apply Online via Parivahan Sewa</h2>
               
                <p>Here's how to apply for your driving license online in India in 2025:</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 1: Visit the Official Portal</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Visit the Parivahan website to apply for your driving licence online:</li>
                    <li>Go to <a href="https://sarathi.parivahan.gov.in/sarathiservice/stateSelection.do" class="for-link" target="_blank">https://sarathi.parivahan.gov.in</a></li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 2: Select Your State</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Choose your state/UT to access local RTO services</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 3: Choose the Service</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Select: <span class="font-weight-700">Apply for Learner's License</span> or <span class="font-weight-700">Apply for Driving License</span> (if you already hold LL)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 4: Fill the Application Form</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Enter personal details like name, address, etc.</li>
                    <li>Choose vehicle class (MCWG, LMV, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Provide emergency contact info</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 5: Upload Required Documents</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Upload scanned copies of identity, address, age proof, and photo</li>
                    <li>Upload Form 1/1A if applicable</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 6: Book Slot for Test</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Schedule a test date and time at the nearest RTO</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 7: Pay the Application Fee</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use UPI, net banking, or credit/debit card</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 8: Appear for the Test</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>For Learner's License: Online written test (traffic signs, rules)</li>
                    <li>For Permanent License: On-ground driving skill test at RTO</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 9: Document Submission</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Carry the original documents and the receipt of the fee payment when you visit the RTO for your driving test.</li>
                    <li>Pass the driving test to obtain a driving license.</li>
                </ul>

